******
[3] Santa Fe province
Date: Wed 23 Jan 2019
Source: El Eco de Sunchales [in Spanish, trans. Mod.TY, edited]
https://elecodesunchales.com.ar/noticia/117478/confirmaron-un-caso-de-hantavirus-en-esperanza


The Ministry of Health, by way of the Office of the Director of the Provincial Promotion and Health, has announced that a case of [a] hantavirus [infection] has been diagnosed in the city of Esperanza. The case has progressed well clinically and currently is in complete remission of symptoms; this case is not related to the current outbreak in Epuyen, since the patient has not traveled nor was in contact with people who have traveled.

[The report goes on to present general information about symptoms and preventive measures for hantavirus infections that have been covered above and in earlier reports. - Mod.TY]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail from HealthMap Alerts
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The specific hantavirus involved in this case is not mentioned.

Santa Fe province is located in the northeast part of Argentina, far from the Andes Mountains and Chubut province where the current outbreak has occurred. Santa Fe province adjoins Entre Rios province where the single case occurred earlier this month (January 2019) (see above and ProMED-mail post Hantavirus - Americas (05): Argentina (4 provinces) RFI 20190121.6266515). - Mod.TY

